1.2 计算 Q 值¶

Q-Learning Q-Learning Value IterationPolicy Iteration-ValueUtility

Q-Learning Q - Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) $$

- $(s_{t},a)$ $a$ $R_{t+1}$ $a$ $s_{t+1}$Q $\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})$$\gamma$

Q $alpha$ Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = (1-\alpha) \times q(s_{t},a) + \alpha \times(R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})) $$

2 $q(s_{t},a)$

$s_1$ u $s_2$ Q u: -24r: -13d: -0.29l: +40$\gamma$ 0.9

$$ \begin{align} q(s_{t},a) & = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) \\ & =(-0.1) + (0.9)*(40) \\ & =(35.9) \end{align} $$

In [31]:
import random
import operator

actions = ['u','r','d','l']
qline = {'u':1.2, 'r':-2.1, 'd':-24.5, 'l':27}
epsilon = 0.3 # 0.3

def choose_action(epsilon):
    if random.uniform(0, 1) <= epsilon: # 
        return random.choice(actions)
    else: 
        return max(qline.items(), key=operator.itemgetter(1))[0]

from Runner import Runner
from Robot import Robot
def train(*args, **kwargs):
#     print(comment)
    print(kwargs.get('comment'))
    g = Maze(maze_size=kwargs.get('maze_size'),trap_number=kwargs.get('trap_number'))
    r = Robot(g,alpha=kwargs.get('alpha'), epsilon0=kwargs.get('epsilon0'), gamma=kwargs.get('gamma'))
    r.set_status(learning=True)

    runner = Runner(r, g)
    runner.run_training(kwargs.get('epoch'), display_direction=True)
    runner.plot_results()
    print('-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------')
# runner.generate_movie(filename = "final1.mp4") #

runner.plot_results()
